default2.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere exist a number of means by which local authorities can seek to influence academies; for example, through meeting with the Chairs of overarching Trusts and regular meetings with regional HMI. There are many examples of positive endeavour on this front
default. In Kent, for example, the local authority has been inviting academies to work in partnership with other schools to create a sustainable, self-improvement school system, which is working well. Despite many examples of positive engagement, difficulties can
default and do arise where, 
defaultfor whatever reason, an academy refuses to engage constructively with the local authority.
